						<summary>

						<p>Nandi pillar set up in the courtyard to the south of the <hi rend="italic">Nandi-maṇḍapa</hi> inside the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 17th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the offering of a lamp to the god Mallikārjuna by Gaṁgajiya and Vīramma.</p>						

						</summary>
